
Various force fields, in both gromacs and Amber format.

Chromophore force fields are included in amber03-star, amber03w and amber03ws

For CHARMM force fields, please see Alex Mackerell's website:
http://mackerell.umaryland.edu/charmm_ff.shtml

Some details:

AMBER:
amber_format/dat/leap... basically this stuff needs to go into the corresponding dat/leap folder of your amber installation.
e.g. for Amber 14, do a git pull and then do something like 'cp -r amber_format/dat/leap blahblah/amber12/dat'. 
The force fields are:
ff03x: amber ff03* (Best, Hummer, JPCB 2009)
ff99SBx: amber ff99SB* (Best, Hummer, JPCB 2009)
ff99SBxildn: amber ff99SB*-ILDN (Best, Hummer, JPCB 2009 and Lindorff-Larsen et al, Proteins, 2011 for ILDN part)
one just does a "source leaprc.ff03x" in leap, e.g., to use ff03*.

GROMACS:
amber03-star: amber ff03*
amber03w: amber ff03w
amber03ws: amber ff03ws


